Noda Doesn’t Want Sales Tax Raised for Rebuilding, Kyodo Says

-- B y   L i l y   N o n o m i y a
-- 
2011-09-16T09:53:17Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-09-16/noda-doesn-t-want-sales-tax-raised-for-rebuilding-kyodo-says.html
Japanese Prime Minister  Yoshihiko
Noda  said he didn’t want  sales tax  to be among levies increased
to pay for reconstruction costs,  Kyodo News  reported, citing
Finance Minister Jun Azumi.  A tax panel headed by Azumi said earlier today that
reconstruction funds would be raised through a combination of
higher sales, income and corporate taxes. The proposal will be
deliberated by ruling and opposition lawmakers.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Lily Nonomiya at 
 lnonomiya@bloomberg.net  